✅ Step 1 — Install PostgreSQL on Your VPS

If PostgreSQL is not installed yet:

Ubuntu / Debian VPS
sudo apt update
sudo apt install postgresql postgresql-contrib

Start service:

sudo systemctl start postgresql
sudo systemctl enable postgresql
✅ Step 2 — Create Database + User (IMPORTANT)

Login to postgres shell:

sudo -u postgres psql

Now create DB + user:

CREATE DATABASE recipe_cms;
CREATE USER strapi_user WITH PASSWORD 'StrongPassword123';
ALTER ROLE strapi_user SET client_encoding TO 'utf8';
ALTER ROLE strapi_user SET default_transaction_isolation TO 'read committed';
ALTER ROLE strapi_user SET timezone TO 'UTC';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE recipe_cms TO strapi_user;

Exit:

\q
✅ Step 3 — Install PostgreSQL Driver in Your Strapi Project

Inside your Strapi project folder:

npm install pg

Strapi uses pg to talk to PostgreSQL.

✅ Step 4 — Replace SQLite Config with PostgreSQL Config

Open:

/config/database.js

Delete SQLite config and replace with this:

const path = require("path");

module.exports = ({ env }) => ({
connection: {
client: "postgres",
connection: {
host: env("DATABASE_HOST", "127.0.0.1"),
port: env.int("DATABASE_PORT", 5432),
database: env("DATABASE_NAME", "recipe_cms"),
user: env("DATABASE_USERNAME", "strapi_user"),
password: env("DATABASE_PASSWORD", "StrongPassword123"),
ssl: env.bool("DATABASE_SSL", false),
},
pool: {
min: 2,
max: 10,
},
acquireConnectionTimeout: 60000,
},
});
✅ Step 5 — Add Environment Variables (VERY IMPORTANT)

Create / edit:

.env

Add:

DATABASE_CLIENT=postgres
DATABASE_HOST=127.0.0.1
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_NAME=recipe_cms
DATABASE_USERNAME=strapi_user
DATABASE_PASSWORD=StrongPassword123
DATABASE_SSL=false
✅ Step 6 — DELETE SQLite File (Critical)

Remove old database file:

rm .tmp/data.db
rm -rf .tmp

SQLite must NOT exist anymore.

✅ Step 7 — Rebuild Strapi (Creates PostgreSQL Tables)

Run:

npm run build
npm run develop

Strapi will now:

✔ Connect to PostgreSQL
✔ Auto-create all tables
✔ Rebuild schema inside Postgres

✅ Step 8 — Recreate Admin User

Because SQLite data is gone, create new admin:

Open browser:

http://your-vps-ip:1337/admin

Create admin again.

⚠️ Step 9 — Migrate Old Data (If Needed)

If you had real data in SQLite, you must export it first.

You can export using:

npm run strapi export
npm run strapi export

